.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH oxiarc-create 1  "oxiarc-create " 
.SH NAME
oxiarc\-create \- Create a new archive
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBoxiarc\-create\fR [\fB\-f\fR|\fB\-\-format\fR] [\fB\-l\fR|\fB\-\-compression\fR] [\fB\-\-compress\-threshold\fR] [\fB\-v\fR|\fB\-\-verbose\fR] [\fB\-n\fR|\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIARCHIVE\fR> [\fIFILES\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Create a new archive
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-f\fR, \fB\-\-format\fR \fI<FORMAT>\fR
Archive format (required for stdout: gzip, xz, bz2, lz4, zst, br, snappy)
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
zip: ZIP archive
.IP \(bu 2
tar: TAR archive
.IP \(bu 2
gzip: GZIP compressed file
.IP \(bu 2
lzh: LZH archive
.IP \(bu 2
xz: XZ compressed file
.IP \(bu 2
lz4: LZ4 compressed file
.IP \(bu 2
bz2: Bzip2 compressed file
.IP \(bu 2
zst: Zstandard compressed file
.IP \(bu 2
br: Brotli compressed file
.IP \(bu 2
snappy: Snappy compressed file
.RE
.TP
\fB\-l\fR, \fB\-\-compression\fR \fI<COMPRESSION>\fR [default: normal]
Compression level
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
store: Store without compression
.IP \(bu 2
fast: Fast compression
.IP \(bu 2
normal: Normal compression (default)
.IP \(bu 2
best: Best compression
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-compress\-threshold\fR \fI<COMPRESS_THRESHOLD>\fR [default: 0]
Files smaller than this (bytes) are stored, not compressed (ZIP only; 0 disables)
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Verbose output
.TP
\fB\-n\fR, \fB\-\-dry\-run\fR
Dry run: show what would be done without creating the archive
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
<\fIARCHIVE\fR>
Output archive file (use "\-" for stdout)
.TP
[\fIFILES\fR]
Files to add to the archive
